rollcalls.summary: The Tax Cuts and Jobs Act of 2017 was a significant overhaul of the U.S. tax code, reducing corporate tax rates from 35% to 21% permanently, lowering individual tax rates temporarily, nearly doubling the standard deduction, and capping the state and local tax (SALT) deduction at $10,000.

rollcalls.vote_document_text: To provide for reconciliation pursuant to titles II and V of the concurrent resolution on the budget for fiscal year 2018.
